frameDefinitions: An Entity has the ability to contain a Theme.
An Agent begins preventing a Captive from moving despite a tendency or desire on the part of the Captive to do so.
An Agent performs some Action which is considered imprudent.
This frame has to do with people (the Residents) residing in Locations, sometimes with a Co-resident.
An Agent matches location with an Entity in order to fulfill some  Purpose.
A Cognizer applies oneself to commit a Pattern to memory, so that the Cognizer would recognize future examples of the Pattern or be able to reproduce it.
frameExamples: Authorities recently <t>captured</t> several suspects who were hiding in a remote mountain area.
I ca n't remember how many times he <t>visited</t> ! DNI
A gaggle of students were frantically <t>memorizing</t> the answers out in the hall.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> whose ability to contain items is assessed.
The <fen>Entity</fen> has the ability to contain the <fen>Theme</fen>, often expressed with a quantity.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Entity</fen> has or had a certain capacity.
The entity which is captured.
The <fen>Agent</fen> brings the <fen>Captive</fen> into custody.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient entity which is responsible for restricting the movement or location of the <fen>Captive</fen>.
When the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.
The individual that performs the <fen>Action</fen>, resulting in danger to themself.
This role denotes the <fen>Action</fen> taken by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> dares to perform the <fen>Action</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> risks doing the <fen>Action</fen>.
The individual(s) that reside at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The place in which somebody resides.
A person or group of people that the resident is staying with or among.
This role refers to the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Resident</fen> resides.
The sentient entity that is temporarily with the <fen>Entity</fen> in order to fulfil some <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The physical entity that is permanently associated with entities or characteristics that the <fen>Agent</fen> wishes to use for some <fen>Purpose</fen>.  During the visit, the <fen>Agent</fen> matches location with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which a visit is made.
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen> during the visit.
The sentient being that focuses on a <fen>Pattern</fen> so that it will remain in the memory.
The phenomenon that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> observes and commits to memory.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
The location wherein the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
